<div id="banner">
	<h1>Like Father Like Son</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Son: Father, can I get this video game.<br />
Father: Not now, I’m in the middle of something.<br />
Son: But why not?<br />
Father: I’m in the middle of something!<br />
Son: Please! I’ll pay for it.<br />
Father: <em>Hold on!</em><br />
Son: But you haven’t even looked at it!</p>

<p><em>&#8230;later, to Mother&#8230;</em></p>

<p>Father: Son is being such a brat lately. He always insists on getting his way.<br />
Mother: I know, we’ll just have to stand firm and show him that whining doesn’t work.</p>

<p><em>&#8230;enough time later that the hypocrisy isn’t immediately evident&#8230;</em></p>

<p>Father: Son, help me build this bookcase.<br />
Son: I’m in the middle of something!<br />
Father: I said help me! Do it right now or I’ll take away your bed.<br />
Son: I’m in the middle of something!<br />
Father: Fine, I’ll take away your bed!<br />
Son: <em>Hold on!</em></p>

<p class="posted">posted June 01, 2003 01:52 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_education">Education</a>)  <a href="000935" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

